item.description:
Let's take advantage of these late summer nights! I played after work rounds all last summer.. I can't tell you of a better, more relaxed way to practice - especially for those beginners out there. 

This date is tentative - let's see how the weather looks a little closer. Also, looking two weeks out, I'm thinking we could set something up for either Tues, Weds, or Thurs of that week. If you want to make it, but Wednesday doesn't work for you - send me a note. I'm flexible at this point.

$12 weekday rate for starts after 6:00pm, and we can easily get 9 holes in. Convenient to exits 12 & 13 on the Mass Pike, perfect if you work or live in the area. Grab dinner then grab your clubs!

http://millwoodgolfcourse.com/

Full listing of rates are here:

http://millwoodgolfcourse.com/rates.html

Updated: 7/11 - Spoke to the clubhouse this afternoon. They don't give actual tee times for twilight rounds - first come, first serve. Let's try to meet between 6:15-6:30. I will send meet-up details to participants on Wednesday.
